## CLI cheat sheet

```bash
sentry whoami
sentry project list
sentry issue list amo-2b/ --query 'is:unresolved' --limit 20
sentry issue view <ISSUE_ID>
sentry issue explain <ISSUE_ID>   # when available
```

Prefer CLI/MCP over scraping the HTML UI ([login wall](https://amo-2b.sentry.io/auth/login/amo-2b/)).

## Seer PR reviews — status

**Enabled 2026-07-10** for `amo-tech-ai/lumina-studio` ([Seer repos](https://amo-2b.sentry.io/settings/seer/repos/?query=lum)): Code Review ON · triggers On New Commit + On Ready For Review.

Live proof (`@sentry review`):

| PR | Seer Code Review check | Inline findings |
|----|------------------------|-----------------|
| #315 (docs) | **pass** (~34s) | 0 |
| #316 (embed fix) | **pass** (~2m34s) | 0 |

**pass + 0 comments** = review finished, no predicted errors (not a failure). Neutral check = findings posted as comments.

Re-enable / troubleshoot: [Seer settings](https://sentry.io/orgredirect/organizations/amo-2b/settings/seer/) · GitHub app **Pull Requests** + **Checks** R/W · keep Seer check **optional** in branch protection.

## Agent workflow — Seer findings on a PR

Load skill **`sentry-pr-code-review`** (not generic PR scraping):

1. Fetch: `gh api repos/amo-tech-ai/lumina-studio/pulls/<N>/comments --paginate --jq '.[] | select(.user.login == "seer-by-sentry[bot]")'`
2. Verify each finding at HEAD (evidence over Seer text)
3. Smallest safe fix; one concern; no docs+code mix
4. Report with the skill’s Resolved / Skipped table
5. Reply/resolve via `pr-workflow` if threads exist

If **zero** Seer comments after `@sentry review`: stop and report setup gap (steps above) — do not invent findings.

## SDK (runtime) — brief

- Config lives under `app/` (`instrumentation.ts`, `sentry.*.config.ts`, `/monitoring` tunnel)
- DSN via Infisical / env — never commit secrets; never `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` for private keys beyond the public DSN pattern Sentry documents
- Smoke: hit example route or `Sentry.captureException` → confirm Issue in amo-2b

